{"questionId":"27889","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Four possible phase portraits for the coupled differential equations&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp;are shown, labelled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A,&nbsp;B,&nbsp;C</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/07570c9f02b6fe13493914f598649e147dc99d04.png\"></p>\n<p>The matrix&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>a</mi></mtd><mtd><mi>b</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>c</mi></mtd><mtd><mi>d</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;has eigenvalues&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>λ</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>λ</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Complete the following table by writing down the letter of the phase portrait that best&nbsp;matches the description.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/0d4b6c0d53082db74a883456be85f43cca8e6894.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/b7acd958fb512a563bec339dd3d92fe576150e1a.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27889","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.12a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Complete the following table by